<subSubSection id="B4D102BCFFE6FFC6FF031E1AFC12FDE3" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FC745137FFE6FFC6FF031E1AFC9EFE88" blockId="8.[192,1440,1871,1929]" lastBlockId="9.[192,1440,221,572]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE6FFC7FF031E1AFEC3F8B8" authorityName="Clemens" authorityYear="1860" box="[232,338,1871,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Amorbia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CEBF8D25FFE6FFC7FF031E1AFEC3F8B8" box="[232,338,1871,1895]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Amorbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was revised by 
<bibRefCitation id="985A2CC6FFE6FFC7FDE71E05FC5FF8B7" author="Phillips-Rodriguez, E. &amp; J. A. Powell" box="[524,974,1872,1896]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" refId="ref8636" refString="Phillips-Rodriguez, E., and J. A. Powell. 2007. Phylogenetic relationships, systematics, and biology of the species of Amorbia Clemens (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae: Sparganothini). Zootaxa 1670, 109 p." type="book" year="2007">Phillips-Rodriguez and Powell (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, who included 29 species in their treatment. They presented host records for 11 of the species, and in cases where one than one rearing was involved, polyphagy seems to be the norm, with a total of 27 plant families documented as hosts for one or more species of 
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FE4919A8FD9DFECA" authorityName="Clemens" authorityYear="1860" box="[418,524,253,277]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Amorbia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CEBF8D25FFE7FFC6FE4919A8FD9DFECA" box="[418,524,253,277]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Amorbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The continued efforts of 
<bibRefCitation id="985A2CC6FFE7FFC6FCAC19ABFB23FEC9" author="Janzen, D. H. &amp; W. Hallwachs" box="[839,1202,254,278]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref8505" refString="Janzen, D. H., and W. Hallwachs. 2009. Dynamic database for an inventory of the macrocaterpillar fauna, and its food plants and parasitoids, of Area de Conservacion Guanacaste (ACG), northwestern Costa Rica (nn-SRNP-nnnnn voucher codes). Available at http: // janzen. sas. upenn. edu. (Last accessed Dec 12 2018.)" type="url" year="2009">Janzen and Hallwachs (2009)</bibRefCitation>
in 
<collectingCountry id="84DC11A7FFE7FFC6FB3119ABFACFFEC9" box="[1242,1374,254,278]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
have added many new hosts but revealed no conspicuous patterns other than polyphagy. During the study in 
<collectingCountry id="84DC11A7FFE7FFC6FF0B186AFED8FE88" box="[224,329,319,343]" name="Ecuador" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, two species of 
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FDE8186AFDFCFE88" authorityName="Clemens" authorityYear="1860" box="[515,621,319,343]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Amorbia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CEBF8D25FFE7FFC6FDE8186AFDFCFE88" box="[515,621,319,343]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Amorbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were reared.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC745137FFE7FFC6FF03180AFA31FE05" blockId="9.[192,1440,221,572]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FF03180AFD42FEA7" authority="Phillips and Powell, 2007" authorityName="Phillips and Powell" authorityYear="2007" box="[232,723,351,376]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Amorbia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cacao">
<emphasis id="CEBF8D25FFE7FFC6FF03180AFE0BFEA8" box="[232,410,351,375]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Amorbia cacao</emphasis>
Phillips and Powell, 2007
</taxonomicName>
, described from specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="84DC11A7FFE7FFC6FBBD1835FB49FEA7" box="[1110,1240,352,376]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="84DC11A7FFE7FFC6FAFB1835FA0AFEA7" box="[1296,1435,352,376]" name="Guatemala" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
, was reported from Yanayacu by 
<bibRefCitation id="985A2CC6FFE7FFC6FDBA18D5FC4BFE46" author="Razowski, J. &amp; J. Wojtusiak" box="[593,986,384,409]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="585 - 603" refId="ref8894" refString="Razowski, J., and J. Wojtusiak. 2010. Some Tortricidae from the East Cordillera in Ecuador reared from larvae in Yanayacu Biological Station in Ecuador (Insecta: Lepidoptera). Genus 21: 585 - 603." type="journal article" year="2010">Razowski and Wojtusiak (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. In 
<collectingCountry id="84DC11A7FFE7FFC6FBE218D4FB01FE47" box="[1033,1168,384,409]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, this species has been reared from 
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FEBF18F4FE4CFE66" authorityName="A.M.C.Dumeril" authorityYear="1805" box="[340,477,417,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FE0D18F4FDFDFE66" authorityName="J.Lindley" authorityYear="1830" box="[486,620,417,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Clusiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Clusiaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FD9D18F4FD7AFE66" authorityName="Lindley &amp; John" authorityYear="1830" box="[630,747,417,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FD1D18F4FC3DFE66" authorityName="Candolle &amp; Candolle" authorityYear="1824" box="[758,940,417,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Flacourtiaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Flacourtiaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FC5D18F4FBCEFE66" authorityName="de Candolle &amp; Perleb" authorityYear="1818" box="[950,1119,417,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Juglandaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Juglandaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FB8218F7FB7AFE66" authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[1129,1259,418,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Lauraceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FB1E18F7FAF9FE66" box="[1269,1384,418,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FF2B1897FD66FE05" authority="(Phillips-Rodriguez and Powell 2007)" baseAuthorityName="Phillips-Rodriguez and Powell" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[192,759,450,474]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sabiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sabiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">
Sabiaceae (
<bibRefCitation id="985A2CC6FFE7FFC6FEAE1897FD7EFE05" author="Phillips-Rodriguez, E. &amp; J. A. Powell" box="[325,751,450,474]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref8636" refString="Phillips-Rodriguez, E., and J. A. Powell. 2007. Phylogenetic relationships, systematics, and biology of the species of Amorbia Clemens (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae: Sparganothini). Zootaxa 1670, 109 p." type="book" year="2007">Phillips-Rodriguez and Powell 2007</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<collectingCountry id="84DC11A7FFE7FFC6FCF41897FC12FE05" box="[799,899,450,474]" name="Ecuador" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
it was reared once from 
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FB4B1894FB7CFE06" authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1184,1261,449,473]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CEBF8D25FFE7FFC6FB4B1894FB7CFE06" box="[1184,1261,449,473]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Rubus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FACA1897FA05FE05" box="[1313,1428,450,474]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC745137FFE7FFC6FF0318B7FC12FDE3" blockId="9.[192,1440,221,572]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FF0318B7FC96FE24" authority="Phillips and Powell, 2007" authorityName="Phillips and Powell" authorityYear="2007" box="[232,775,482,507]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Amorbia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colubrana">
<emphasis id="CEBF8D25FFE7FFC6FF0318B7FE43FE25" box="[232,466,482,506]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Amorbia colubrana</emphasis>
Phillips and Powell, 2007
</taxonomicName>
was reported from 
<collectingCountry id="84DC11A7FFE7FFC6FC0618B7FBF2FE25" box="[1005,1123,482,506]" name="Colombia" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="84DC11A7FFE7FFC6FB8618B7FB47FE25" box="[1133,1238,482,506]" name="Ecuador" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="84DC11A7FFE7FFC6FAF818B6FAC1FE25" box="[1299,1360,483,506]" name="Peru" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Peru</collectingCountry>
, above about 
<quantity id="3B33FCD2FFE7FFC6FEE61B56FEF6FDC4" box="[269,359,515,539]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</quantity>
elevation (
<bibRefCitation id="985A2CC6FFE7FFC6FE051B56FC39FDC4" author="Phillips-Rodriguez, E. &amp; J. A. Powell" box="[494,936,515,539]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref8636" refString="Phillips-Rodriguez, E., and J. A. Powell. 2007. Phylogenetic relationships, systematics, and biology of the species of Amorbia Clemens (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae: Sparganothini). Zootaxa 1670, 109 p." type="book" year="2007">Phillips-Rodriguez and Powell 2007</bibRefCitation>
). No larval hosts were previously known. In 
<collectingCountry id="84DC11A7FFE7FFC6FF091B71FED9FDE3" box="[226,328,548,572]" name="Ecuador" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
it was reared once from 
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FD9C1B76FD24FDE4" authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1821" box="[631,693,547,571]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CEBF8D25FFE7FFC6FD9C1B76FD24FDE4" box="[631,693,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Pilea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName id="3BCB2AB4FFE7FFC6FD041B71FCE6FDE3" authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[751,887,548,572]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Urticaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
